This paper discusses the optimization of a computational fluid dynamics (CFD) application, which is a common topic in the computer engineering (cs.CE) sub-category. The use of high-level frameworks and parallel implementations also suggests a potential fit for the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also discusses the challenges of data organization and movement, which could fall under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Additionally, the use of optimizations for different parallel architectures suggests a potential fit for the modeling and simulation (cs.MS) sub-category, as well as the numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-category.
